FILEVAULT STATUS REPORT FORM
----------------------------
The following form can be used to share with a FileVault wizard in case you need help.
He/she will ask for this information anyway: 

Observed issue: 

FileVault enablement method used: 

Admin account used to run ‘sudo’ commands where needed: 

GENERAL INFO: 
-------------
Output of ‘diskutil apfs listusers /‘ : 


Output of ‘sudo fdesetup list -extended’:  


Output of ‘fdesetup status’:  


Output of ‘sudo fdesetup showdeferralinfo’:  


Output of ‘sudo profiles status -type bootstraptoken’: 


SPECIFIC USER SECURE TOKEN INFO:
--------------------------------

Output of ‘sysadminctl interactive -secureTokenStatus username’ :


or when executing scripted or via ssh: 

Output of‘sysadminctl -adminUser adminusername -adminPassword adminpassword -secureTokenStatus username’: 


(Optional) Output of ‘dscl . -read /Users/username AuthenticationAuthority’: 




 
